<subsection xml:id="subsec-Place-Value-of-digits-in-a-number">
        <title>Place Value of digits in a number</title>
            
          <p> Have you ever wondered what the digits in big numbers really mean? When you see a number like <em>85 147 000</em>, each digit is important and its value depends on where it is in the number.
          </p>
          <p> This is what we call <em> place value</em>. Each place tells us how much a digit is worth. Let’s explore this together!
          </p>

            <activity>
              <statement>
                <p>Here's a real-world example.</p> 
                <p>Pembe Flour Milling Factory in Nairobi produced:</p>
                <p><em>85 147 000 kg</em> of maize flour in 2023,  and another <em>120 568 720 kg</em> of maize flour in 2024. </p>
                <p> </p>

                <p>That’s a lot of flour! But let’s slow down and look at the numbers more closely.</p>

